fr.sii.ogham.spring.email

Class AbstractSpringSendGridConfigurer

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.spring.email.AbstractSpringSendGridConfigurer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configurer<MessagingBuilder>, MessagingConfigurer, SpringMessagingConfigurer, org.springframework.core.Ordered
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SpringSendGridV2Configurer, SpringSendGridV4Configurer

    public abstract class AbstractSpringSendGridConfigurer
extends Object
implements SpringMessagingConfigurer
    Integrates with Spring SendGrid by using Spring properties defined with prefix spring.sendgrid (see SendGridProperties). If both Spring property and Ogham property is defined, Ogham property is used. For example, if the file application.properties contains the following configuration: 
     spring.sendgrid.api-key=foo
 ogham.email.sendgrid.api-key=bar
    The SendGridSender implementation will use foo to connect to the SendGrid service.

    This configurer is also useful to support property naming variants (see Relaxed Binding).
